Stock Transportation is a Canadian school bus contractor. Based in Newmarket, Ontario, the company provides student transportation services for 28 school districts in Ontario, Nova Scotia and Alberta.
Founded in 1958 by Jeff and Jerry Stock, part of the bus business was sold to Travelways; in 1979, the family resumed school bus operations. In 2002, the company was acquired by National Express in July 2002. Stock Transportation recently purchased Deluxe Coach Lines, Alouette Bus Lines of North Bay and as of January 31, RL Smith Transportation of Edmonton.
